The `APIRoutes` in an `APIRouter` commonly share the same tags. This PR helps in documenting different routes under the same context. For example, this now enables:
```python
data_router = APIRouter(tags=['data'])

@data_router.get('/')
def get_data():
    ...

@data_router.post('/')
def post_data(...):
    ...
```
, instead of:
```python
data_router = APIRouter()

@data_router.get('/', tags=['data'])
def get_data():
    ...

@data_router.post('/', tags=['data'])
def post_data(...):
    ...
```


I can add tests and documentation if the maintainers are fine with this approach.

